                    <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
                    <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>From the vSphere Client select the ESXi Host and go to Configuration &gt;&gt; Networking &gt;&gt; Select properties on the virtual switch &gt;&gt; Select the port group and click Edit.  Change the VLAN ID to a non-native VLAN and click OK.

or

From a PowerCLI command prompt while connected to the ESXi host run the following command:

Get-VirtualPortGroup -Name "portgroup name" | Set-VirtualPortGroup -VLanId "New VLAN#"</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
